On 9/8/03 5:59 AM, "Messa, Corbett (IndSys, GEFanuc, NA)"
<Corbett.Messa(-at-)gefanuc.com> wrote:

> Speaking of flushing the brake system, this is on my list of things to do
> soon. How does everyone else do this? I read the procedure on Type2.com, but
> I wanted to hear from others on the list and see how they have done it and
> what problems they ran into. It looks like the easiest would be to get some
> type of one way setup so that I can do this alone. Does anyone know where to
> get the proper kit for a 73 Westy?

Bar none, this is the easiest way to do it alone:

http://www.motiveproducts.com/

Model 1104 screws right onto the bus brake fluid reservoir. You fill it,
pump it and then walk around to each wheel in order of of longest brake line
to shortest (rear pass, rear driver, front pass, front driver) bleeding and
you're done in 15 minutes.

